c_ea_e_biz_01_01.name: Burnout Bully
c_ea_e_biz_01_01.explanation:
A businessman who works for a shady
company. The crushing stress of work
has brought out his violent side.

c_ea_e_biz_02_01.name: Capitalist Punisher
c_ea_e_biz_02_01.explanation:
A bad-tempered businessman who
recklessly picks fights and then demands
compensation. He's really strapped for cash.

c_ea_e_biz_03_01.name: Dotcombatant
c_ea_e_biz_03_01.explanation:
A shady "businessman" looking for investment
capital. Has a real knack for web design,
at least—judging by his scam sites.

c_ea_e_drk_01_01.name: Hammeredhead
c_ea_e_drk_01_01.explanation:
Wanders town drunk off his ass. Watch out,
though—he'll blindly flail a weapon at
anyone who gets close.

c_ea_e_drk_02_01.name: Beerserker
c_ea_e_drk_02_01.explanation:
An even more violent drunk. He's been at
the center of many an altercation, but
apparently doesn't remember a thing.

c_ea_e_drk_03_01.name: Knight of the Cask
c_ea_e_drk_03_01.explanation:
Really into period films. Insists everyone
call him "General" when drunk. Once he
goes wild, nobody can stop him.

c_ea_e_drk_04_01.name: Urbane Legend
c_ea_e_drk_04_01.explanation:
A man known as a hero in many bars.
Charms all onlookers with his mysterious
party tricks.

c_ea_e_hol_01_01.name: Battle Bum
c_ea_e_hol_01_01.explanation:
An eye-stingingly pungent street-dweller.
Can't do much damage on his own, so
he attacks by calling a crowd of his friends.

c_ea_e_hol_02_01.name: Hungry Hungry Homeless
c_ea_e_hol_02_01.explanation:
A street-dweller who's gotten hungry
enough to turn violent. They lose control
when they smell food.

c_ea_e_hol_03_01.name: Arch-Vagrant
c_ea_e_hol_03_01.explanation:
A man who rules over the city's homeless
population. Years of attuning to the streets
gave him the power to exude any stench.

c_ea_e_hol_04_01.name: Invested Vagabond
c_ea_e_hol_04_01.explanation:
A street survivalist who rarely shows
himself. Despite his appearance, he's
actually fairly rich.

c_ea_e_hos_01_01.name: Biting Barker
c_ea_e_hos_01_01.explanation:
A devious barker trying to lure customers
to a ripoff host club. Tends to target
innocent women who he can fast-talk.

c_ea_e_hos_02_01.name: Hostile Host
c_ea_e_hos_02_01.explanation:
A supporting host that works at a ripoff
host club. Nobody requests him much, so
they have him moonlighting as a barker.

c_ea_e_hos_03_01.name: Host with the Most
c_ea_e_hos_03_01.explanation:
A veteran host of a ripoff host club. He's
willing to do whatever it takes to be the
best host in town.

c_ea_e_hos_04_01.name: Heavenly Host
c_ea_e_hos_04_01.explanation:
The top host of a ripoff host club. His
twisted, egomaniacal outlook makes
him a genuine threat.

c_ea_e_chp_01_01.name: Punkling
c_ea_e_chp_01_01.explanation:
A punk running with a certain gang.
Used as expendable frontline fodder in
their raids.

c_ea_e_chp_02_01.name: Steamed Punk
c_ea_e_chp_02_01.explanation:
A thug known to be a skilled fighter even
among his peers. Trying to punch his
way to the top.

c_ea_e_chp_03_01.name: Overpunk
c_ea_e_chp_03_01.explanation:
A capable punk who's earned the respect
of the entire gang. Some call him an icon
of the punk world.

c_ea_e_chp_04_01.name: Mohawk Emperor
c_ea_e_chp_04_01.explanation:
A legendary punk who boasts unrivaled
strength, even among the outlaws. Above
all else, hates when his hair wears out.

c_ea_e_fig_01_01.name: Hands Thrower
c_ea_e_fig_01_01.explanation:
An amateur fighter who hones his skills
through street fighting. He's been really
into MMA lately.

c_ea_e_fig_02_01.name: Wrestlemaniac
c_ea_e_fig_02_01.explanation:
A professional martial artist affiliated with
a mysterious underground tournament.
Excels at grappling over direct strikes.

c_ea_e_fig_03_01.name: Masque Raider
c_ea_e_fig_03_01.explanation:
A masked wrestler affiliated with a certain
independent group. Even outside the ring,
he's an unpredictable, volatile threat.

c_ea_e_fig_04_01.name: Ultimate Champion
c_ea_e_fig_04_01.explanation:
Legendary masked wrestler. While he's
mastered several martial arts, he claims
pro wrestling is the strongest style.

c_ea_e_gag_01_01.name: Color Gangsman
c_ea_e_gag_01_01.explanation:
Part of a group called the Color Gang.
Always with his crew, fighting to seize or
defend turf in the city.

c_ea_e_gag_02_01.name: Mad Gangsman
c_ea_e_gag_02_01.explanation:
One of the guys behind the Color Gang's
more disruptive endeavors. Carries many
self-defense items, such as a katana.

c_ea_e_gag_03_01.name: Elite Gangsman
c_ea_e_gag_03_01.explanation:
A frontline ace of the Color Gang. Knows
his way around a fight. Quick, brutal, and
ready to take his rivals down.

c_ea_e_gag_04_01.name: Boss Gangsman
c_ea_e_gag_04_01.explanation:
Keeps the Color Gang in check. The guy's
so tough, he's never lost a one-on-one
fight with any of the crew.

c_ea_e_trb_01_01.name: Tribesman
c_ea_e_trb_01_01.explanation:
Part of an armed group called Tribal that's
been expanding their influence in recent
years. Also deals in underground business.

c_ea_e_trb_02_01.name: Tribesguard
c_ea_e_trb_02_01.explanation:
Something like a bouncer within Tribal.
Often seen supervising at the locations of
underground business deals.

c_ea_e_trb_03_01.name: Tribesbrute
c_ea_e_trb_03_01.explanation:
A true warrior among the Tribal. If there's
ever trouble within the group, he quells
it himself through sheer force.

c_ea_e_trb_04_01.name: Tribeschief
c_ea_e_trb_04_01.explanation:
The boss that leads Tribal. The sinuous
pattern of his unusual tattoos strikes fear
into the hearts of his enemies.

c_ea_e_gun_01_01.name: Assassin
c_ea_e_gun_01_01.explanation:
An agent of the underworld who takes
contracts to kill. If you can pull it off, the
targets are apparently worth hefty payloads.

c_ea_e_gun_02_01.name: Primal Psychopath
c_ea_e_gun_02_01.explanation:
An assassin in a deranged state of mind.
Convinced he's being targeted, he swings
his blade with desperate abandon.

c_ea_e_gun_03_01.name: One-Hitman
c_ea_e_gun_03_01.explanation:
A skilled assassin said to take out his
targets with one hit. With a sharp dagger
and keen aim, he goes right for the vitals.

c_ea_e_gun_04_01.name: The Fist
c_ea_e_gun_04_01.explanation:
This assassin feels his life's purpose is
to beat his foes down. With every punch
thrown, he flies further into his frenzy.

c_ea_e_toj_01_01.name: Some Other Yakuza
c_ea_e_toj_01_01.explanation:
Do you realize how many yakuza are in this
city? Who has time to categorize all of them?
Just take my word for it: they're all Sujimon.

c_ea_e_ykz_01_01.name: Newbie Yakuza
c_ea_e_ykz_01_01.explanation:
A fresh yakuza who's just joined a minor
family. Dreams of working his way up the
ranks through his criminal deeds.

c_ea_e_ykz_02_01.name: Ornery Yakuza
c_ea_e_ykz_02_01.explanation:
An out-of-control yakuza from a lesser-
known family. Hoping to get scouted by
the Omi Alliance.

c_ea_e_ykz_03_01.name: Eloquent Yakuza
c_ea_e_ykz_03_01.explanation:
An intelligent yakuza affiliated with a lesser-
known family. He secures funds through
financial savvy he picked up in college.

c_ea_e_ykz_04_01.name: Grizzled Yakuza
c_ea_e_ykz_04_01.explanation:
A veteran yakuza. Scouted by the Tojo Clan,
but chose to stick with his minor family.
They let him get away with anything.

c_ea_e_ykz_05_01.name: Scarred Yakuza
c_ea_e_ykz_05_01.explanation:
A heavily-scarred yakuza from a lesser-
known family. One look is enough to tell
you how much bloodshed he's survived.

c_ea_e_wrk_01_01.name: Demolitioneer
c_ea_e_wrk_01_01.explanation:
An unruly worker in the demolition
industry. Always in a bad mood, he can
make a real mess with that hammer.

c_ea_e_wrk_02_01.name: Clobberjack
c_ea_e_wrk_02_01.explanation:
A worker that keeps starting fights at the
demolition locations. If he doesn't like
something, it gets the hammer.

c_ea_e_wrk_03_01.name: Sledgeharmer
c_ea_e_wrk_03_01.explanation:
A dangerous worker with destructive urges
and a hammer. Liable to start wrecking
anything he sets his eyes on.

c_ea_e_wrk_04_01.name: Batterer out of Hell
c_ea_e_wrk_04_01.explanation:
A mysterious wrecker. With his buff arms
and brutal strikes, he's determined to crush
anything in his path.

c_ea_e_rbb_01_01.name: Pro Pickpocket
c_ea_e_rbb_01_01.explanation:
A criminal who subtly sneaks wallets out
of the pockets of passersby. You might
never even notice you've been hit.

c_ea_e_rbb_02_01.name: Break-and-Entryman
c_ea_e_rbb_02_01.explanation:
A criminal who illegally enters buildings
and steals valuables. Has ties to a certain
organized theft group.

c_ea_e_rbb_03_01.name: Cutpurse
c_ea_e_rbb_03_01.explanation:
A bandit with an old-fashioned look. Uses
mysterious techniques to confuse his mark
before taking their valuables.

c_ea_e_rbb_04_01.name: King of Thieves
c_ea_e_rbb_04_01.explanation:
Descendant of an infamous thief from the
Azuchi-Momoyama period. Steals from
the wicked and gives to the poor.

c_ea_e_chn_01_01.name: Chinese Mafioso
c_ea_e_chn_01_01.explanation:
Fighter from a Chinese Mafia. Armed
with a vicious claw, he slices his foes to
ribbons.

c_ea_e_chn_02_01.name: Chinese Mafia Officer
c_ea_e_chn_02_01.explanation:
Officer of a Chinese Mafia. Swift and
powerful enough to bring his foes to the
ground—and sink his claws into their vitals.

c_ea_e_chn_03_01.name: Chinese Mafia Boss
c_ea_e_chn_03_01.explanation:
The boss of a Chinese Mafia. His unique
claws are lethal enough, but a coating
of venom makes them deadlier.

c_ea_e_kun_01_01.name: Kung Fu Disciple
c_ea_e_kun_01_01.explanation:
A student of Chinese martial arts. Hired
by an organized crime group, he works
for them as a bouncer.

c_ea_e_kun_02_01.name: Kung Fu Master
c_ea_e_kun_02_01.explanation:
After long years of training, this man has
become a true master of kung fu.

c_ea_e_kun_03_01.name: Qigong Master
c_ea_e_kun_03_01.explanation:
An elder who has learned not only kung fu,
but the art of qigong. His techniques look
like psychic abilities to the untrained.

c_ea_e_kun_04_01.name: Dragon King
c_ea_e_kun_04_01.explanation:
A legendary martial artist. After years of
rigorous exercise and ascetic practice,
his body has become as tough as steel.

c_ea_e_cok_01_01.name: Pressured Cooker
c_ea_e_cok_01_01.explanation:
Chef that works at a Chinese restaurant
with a bad rep. Ready to kick the ass of
anyone who criticizes his cooking.

c_ea_e_cok_02_01.name: Mystery Meatsmith
c_ea_e_cok_02_01.explanation:
This shady cook's food is made from...
ingredients. Those who meet him tend
to mysteriously go missing afterwards.

c_ea_e_cok_03_01.name: Ironclad Chef
c_ea_e_cok_03_01.explanation:
A head chef who keeps his rowdy kitchen
crew in line. An absolutely abysmal cook,
but a deft master of the knife.

c_ea_e_jug_01_01.name: Shruggler
c_ea_e_jug_01_01.explanation:
Doesn't care about getting permission for his
performances. Things get ugly if anyone
tries to disrupt his show.

c_ea_e_jug_02_01.name: Thuggler
c_ea_e_jug_02_01.explanation:
A street performer who juggles knives.
Many have lodged complaints against him,
especially after his antics get people injured.

c_ea_e_jug_03_01.name: Druggler
c_ea_e_jug_03_01.explanation:
A bizarre street performer who juggles
drug torches. He seems to enjoy the
thrill of playing with fire.

c_ea_e_jug_04_01.name: Juggle-O
c_ea_e_jug_04_01.explanation:
A legendary street performer who handles
burning torches. A deviant who thrills in
the sound of onlookers screaming.

c_ea_e_phk_01_01.name: Slasher
c_ea_e_phk_01_01.explanation:
An unhinged psycho who slashes at
passersby with a knife. In terms of
physical strength, he's not that capable.

c_ea_e_phk_02_01.name: Paralyticist
c_ea_e_phk_02_01.explanation:
Sneaks behind passersby and knocks them
unconscious with a stun gun. Keeps a lot
more self-defense tools on him, too.

c_ea_e_phk_03_01.name: Black Blade
c_ea_e_phk_03_01.explanation:
An unknown slasher at the center of a
number of violent incidents. Eyewitnesses
all call him "the man in black."

c_ea_e_phk_04_01.name: Dismemberer
c_ea_e_phk_04_01.explanation:
A dangerous butcher inspired by serial
killers from gory horror films. Has a day
job at a meat factory.

c_ea_e_phk_05_01.name: Jack the Ripper
c_ea_e_phk_05_01.explanation:
Descendant of the legendary slasher who
struck fear into all of England. Slices into
opponents with inhuman ferocity.

c_ea_e_doc_01_01.name: Quackpot
c_ea_e_doc_01_01.explanation:
Half-asses medical exams and rips off his
patients. Those who complain get
silenced with violence and cruelty.

c_ea_e_doc_02_01.name: Heartless Surgeon
c_ea_e_doc_02_01.explanation:
This anatomist had his medical license
revoked due to his connections with the
criminal underworld. Uses various drugs.

c_ea_e_doc_03_01.name: Dr. Black
c_ea_e_doc_03_01.explanation:
An infamous back-alley doctor of the
underworld, he's mastered a multitude
of medical disciplines. A god with a scalpel.

c_ea_e_acp_01_01.name: Sneak-a-tack
c_ea_e_acp_01_01.explanation:
A sly acupuncturist with a penchant for
pranking his patients. Sticks needles into
entirely unnecessary places.

c_ea_e_acp_02_01.name: Pierceologist
c_ea_e_acp_02_01.explanation:
An acupuncturist studying body modifications
through acupuncture points. When things
get dicey, he sticks needles in himself.

c_ea_e_acp_03_01.name: Mad Casey
c_ea_e_acp_03_01.explanation:
Perverted acupuncturist that loves hidden
cameras. Has a paid stream for voyeurs
to watch him work on his patients.

c_ea_e_acp_04_01.name: Weltraiser
c_ea_e_acp_04_01.explanation:
A pierceologist who has succeeded in the
ultimate body modification. He no longer
feels external pain.

c_ea_e_fod_01_01.name: Dine-and-Dasher
c_ea_e_fod_01_01.explanation:
Part of the dine-and-dash group talked
about around town. They're so strong,
restaurants can't do much to stop them.

c_ea_e_fod_02_01.name: Snack-and-Sprinter
c_ea_e_fod_02_01.explanation:
Part of the dine-and-dash group, and an
acclaimed speed-eater. He's gone before
the waiters even realize he's eaten.

c_ea_e_fod_03_01.name: Chomp-and-Charger
c_ea_e_fod_03_01.explanation:
A glutton who bumbles around looking for
fatty foods. If he gets even a little too
hungry, the berserker rage kicks in.

c_ea_e_fod_04_01.name: Noblesse Obesity
c_ea_e_fod_04_01.explanation:
A devotee of all things meat, this scourge
of the buffet line deflects all kinds of attacks
with a protective layer of thick blubber.

c_ea_e_hit_01_01.name: Hitjourneyman
c_ea_e_hit_01_01.explanation:
A hitman who shoots from afar with a
bowgun. He's still learning, and frankly,
he's not a great shot.

c_ea_e_hit_02_01.name: Urban Ranger
c_ea_e_hit_02_01.explanation:
A man who chooses to have no home but
the mean city streets. Loves to hunt
with his bowgun.

c_ea_e_hit_03_01.name: Notorious V.I.P.
c_ea_e_hit_03_01.explanation:
A top-notch hitman, he's a big name
among his peers in the underworld. Hates
having people stand behind him.

c_ea_e_hit_04_01.name: Ghillie Man
c_ea_e_hit_04_01.explanation:
A mysterious hitman who stays hidden in
a ghillie suit. Pops unexpectedly out of the
underbrush to make his move.

c_ea_e_amy_01_01.name: Military Buffed
c_ea_e_amy_01_01.explanation:
An extreme military otaku. Typically found
wandering around loaded up with tons of
dangerous equipment.

c_ea_e_amy_02_01.name: One-Man Army
c_ea_e_amy_02_01.explanation:
An otaku who sees himself as the hero this
city needs. Definitely been watching too many
war movies, but surprisingly competent.

c_ea_e_amy_03_01.name: Master and Commando
c_ea_e_amy_03_01.explanation:
A mercenary with kill counts on battlegrounds
all across the world. Now that he's home,
he's got all kinds of underworld contracts.

c_ea_e_amy_04_01.name: Arminator
c_ea_e_amy_04_01.explanation:
An enigmatic assassin. Rumors say that
he's something more than human, created
in a military lab.

c_ea_e_bou_01_01.name: Biker Cavalier
c_ea_e_bou_01_01.explanation:
Causes noise pollution with modded bikes
and cars. There used to be a lot more of
them around, but they're in decline.

c_ea_e_bou_02_01.name: Biker Vanguard
c_ea_e_bou_02_01.explanation:
The most reckless guy the biker gang's got.
Excels at charging into enemy territory,
even knowing it's suicidal.

c_ea_e_bou_03_01.name: Biker Boss
c_ea_e_bou_03_01.explanation:
The boss that keeps the gang in line.
Many view him as an icon, but he's been
thinking about retirement a lot lately.

c_ea_e_frg_01_01.name: Stern Stranger
c_ea_e_frg_01_01.explanation:
Came to Japan to make money, but found
criminal distractions instead. Showing up
a lot in the business quarters at night.

c_ea_e_frg_02_01.name: Big Dog
c_ea_e_frg_02_01.explanation:
A bouncer who accompanies foreigners
making illegal deals. Thanks to his size,
most people know him simply as "Big Dog."

c_ea_e_frg_03_01.name: Bouncer
c_ea_e_frg_03_01.explanation:
A bouncer at a club that's a hub
for shady dealings. Tough enough that
nobody's seen him lose a fight.

c_ea_e_frg_04_01.name: Big Payback
c_ea_e_frg_04_01.explanation:
A mysterious contractor called in by
mafias to exact revenge. Punches
foes down until they stop moving.

c_ea_e_hac_01_01.name: Technomancer
c_ea_e_hac_01_01.explanation:
Part of a group with excellent computer
tech and hacking skills. They wear masks
to keep themselves anonymous.

c_ea_e_hac_02_01.name: Black Hat Wizard
c_ea_e_hac_02_01.explanation:
A respected authority among the hackers.
Plucks national secrets from the internet
and leaks them to the underworld.

c_ea_e_hac_03_01.name: Nameless
c_ea_e_hac_03_01.explanation: A shadowy hacker capable of taking control of any network worldwide.

c_ea_e_sel_01_01.name: Smugglebug
c_ea_e_sel_01_01.explanation:
Typically found selling chintzy accessories
on the streets, but illegally sells dangerous
drugs behind the scenes.

c_ea_e_sel_02_01.name: The Mule
c_ea_e_sel_02_01.explanation:
A smuggler who imports shady drugs from
overseas. Has a smuggling contingency
plan for every orifice.

c_ea_e_sel_03_01.name: Scarredface
c_ea_e_sel_03_01.explanation:
Boss of a foreign smuggling business.
Also a gifted pharmacologist, he sells and
manufactures drugs he himself developed.

c_ea_e_con_01_01.name: False Alarmist
c_ea_e_con_01_01.explanation:
Causes traffic accidents on purpose and
demands compensation... which is then
wasted at the nearest gambling hall.

c_ea_e_con_02_01.name: Phony Bookie
c_ea_e_con_02_01.explanation:
Runs his own private bookmaking business,
and makes a killing. Great at confusing
customers with half-assed predictions.

c_ea_e_con_03_01.name: Master Gambler
c_ea_e_con_03_01.explanation:
An incredibly lucky man and a gambler
seemingly on an eternal winning streak.
His predictions have never been wrong.

c_ea_e_rap_01_01.name: Poser
c_ea_e_rap_01_01.explanation:
A man who "takes inspiration" from the
foreign rapper lifestyle, but has absolutely
no rapping ability. Particular about his looks.

c_ea_e_rap_02_01.name: Freestylist
c_ea_e_rap_02_01.explanation:
A skilled freestyle rapper. He can dish out
rhymes and pain in equal measure, even
at the same time.

c_ea_e_rap_03_01.name: Diss Tracker
c_ea_e_rap_03_01.explanation:
Focuses on dissing his opponent. Since
he totally ignores rhythm or flow, though,
it's basically plain old verbal abuse.

c_ea_e_rap_04_01.name: King Joe
c_ea_e_rap_04_01.explanation:
A legend of the street dancing world.
His moves are so sublime, nobody can
turn down a chance to dance with him.

c_ea_e_sct_01_01.name: Pimpmaster
c_ea_e_sct_01_01.explanation:
A devious douchebag who deceives
innocent women and sells them into the sex
industry. Formerly a run-of-the-mill punk.

c_ea_e_sct_02_01.name: Roguish Recruiter
c_ea_e_sct_02_01.explanation:
Lies about being from a major production
company to sell girls into the sex industry.
Prowls places with lots of foot traffic.

c_ea_e_sct_03_01.name: Shakedowner
c_ea_e_sct_03_01.explanation:
Man who goes around collecting debts on
orders from the Maneating Loan Shark.
Runs down and threatens all debtors.

c_ea_e_sct_04_01.name: Maneating Loan Shark
c_ea_e_sct_04_01.explanation:
A malicious moneylender who loans out
cash with absurd interest rates and then
corners debtors. Values money over life.

c_ea_e_ars_01_01.name: Bomb Bug
c_ea_e_ars_01_01.explanation:
Sneaks into empty (or mostly-empty)
buildings, and destroys them with exploding
bottles. Carries a lot. Skilled with fire.

c_ea_e_ars_02_01.name: Iceonist
c_ea_e_ars_02_01.explanation:
A criminal who carries liquid nitrogen
around to freeze random things. Loves
freezing and collecting living creatures.

c_ea_e_ars_03_01.name: Bombardier
c_ea_e_ars_03_01.explanation:
This terrorist tries to bomb places with
his homemade explosives. Owing to poor
quality, though, many of them end up duds.

c_ea_e_thg_01_01.name: Escapist
c_ea_e_thg_01_01.explanation:
Was locked away for years after a theft,
but has now escaped—unable to take
prison life. Extremely quick to flee.

c_ea_e_thg_02_01.name: Feral Felon
c_ea_e_thg_02_01.explanation:
Once locked away for heinous crimes.
The depth of his cruelty earned him
special restraints, but he's broken free.

c_ea_e_thg_03_01.name: Twisted Mind
c_ea_e_thg_03_01.explanation:
A legendarily eccentric serial killer and
most-wanted criminal. Has very high IQ,
and skilled at psychological manipulation.

c_ea_e_bxe_01_01.name: Unboxer
c_ea_e_bxe_01_01.explanation:
A punk with a membership at a boxing
gym. Uses his newly-learned boxing skills
in streetfights.

c_ea_e_bxe_02_01.name: Headguardian
c_ea_e_bxe_02_01.explanation:
Once a wannabe, he's stepping up his
game and improving his defenses. That
equipment is technically gym property.

c_ea_e_bxe_03_01.name: Prizedfighter
c_ea_e_bxe_03_01.explanation:
A former pro boxer who had his license
revoked for cases of assault. He currently
works as a bouncer in the underworld.

c_ea_e_bxe_04_01.name: The Death Knuckle
c_ea_e_bxe_04_01.explanation:
Equipped with the G-B-H-G, the deadliest
weapon in the underground arena. This
boxer's overwhelming power breaks guards.

c_ea_e_zea_01_01.name: Hollow Follower
c_ea_e_zea_01_01.explanation:
Follower of a shady religious group that
worships a chicken as their god. Received
a special baptism from the founder.

c_ea_e_zea_02_01.name: Shady Minister
c_ea_e_zea_02_01.explanation:
Minister of a shady religious group that
worships a chicken as their god. Attracts
new acolytes through charisma and rhetoric.

c_ea_e_zea_03_01.name: Fishy Founder
c_ea_e_zea_03_01.explanation:
Founder of a shady religious group that
worships a chicken as their god. Spouts
poultry-inspired revelations (ie. bullshit).

c_ea_e_zea_04_01.name: Munanugget Messiah
c_ea_e_zea_04_01.explanation:
The living god of a shady religious group
that worships a chicken. Said to lay
miraculous, immaculately-conceived eggs.

c_ea_e_psy_01_01.name: Spirited Medium
c_ea_e_psy_01_01.explanation:
A man attuned to a mysterious spiritual
power, he can commune with ghosts,
or even let them possess his body.

c_ea_e_psy_02_01.name: Blind Seer
c_ea_e_psy_02_01.explanation:
A man with psychic powers unexplainable
by modern science. Uses psychokinesis
to hamper his opponent's movements.

c_ea_e_psy_03_01.name: Mister Six
c_ea_e_psy_03_01.explanation:
A professor who studied psychic ability
and awakened his sixth sense. Controls
powers beyond human understanding.

c_ea_e_gad_01_01.name: Pocketing Watchman
c_ea_e_gad_01_01.explanation:
A corrupt guard who steals from the very
establishment he's guarding. Any witnesses
get a faceful of baton.

c_ea_e_gad_02_01.name: Officer of the Lawless
c_ea_e_gad_02_01.explanation:
A charlatan dressed as a lawman. Part of
a burglary ring that invades and robs
homes while "on patrol."

c_ea_e_gad_03_01.name: False Security
c_ea_e_gad_03_01.explanation:
Part of a group of thieves. Masquerading
as security officers, they creep up on bank
transport vehicles and drive off with them.

c_ea_e_gad_04_01.name: Subjugation-kun
c_ea_e_gad_04_01.explanation:
A next-generation security developed by
a security company. Some models were
stolen and reprogrammed.

c_ea_e_bbf_01_01.name: Baseball Diehard
c_ea_e_bbf_01_01.explanation:
An overzealous fan. If his team loses, he
flies into a frenzy, rioting in the streets.
Gentle as a lamb when they win, though.

c_ea_e_bbf_02_01.name: Rabblerouser
c_ea_e_bbf_02_01.explanation:
A more extreme variety of baseball fan.
Post-match rioting's basically guaranteed,
whether out of triumph or rage.

c_ea_e_bbf_03_01.name: Massacre Mascot
c_ea_e_bbf_03_01.explanation:
A rioter wearing the team's mascot mask.
Wielding a molotov, this faceless agent
of chaos spreads panic in his community.

c_ea_e_bbp_01_01.name: Shade Thrower
c_ea_e_bbp_01_01.explanation:
A pitcher on an aggressive sandlotter team,
he hurls more verbal abuse than pitches.
Quick to resort to violence.

c_ea_e_bbp_02_01.name: Hands Catcher
c_ea_e_bbp_02_01.explanation:
A catcher on an aggressive sandlotter team,
he injures opposing team members with
forceful blocking. Has high defenses.

c_ea_e_bbp_03_01.name: Assaulting Batter
c_ea_e_bbp_03_01.explanation:
A fast foreign batter from an aggressive
sandlotter team, he takes the field when
things get dicey for his teammates.

c_ea_e_cln_01_01.name: Purger of Filth
c_ea_e_cln_01_01.explanation:
Obsessed with cleanliness. Has an urge
to cleanse anyone who falls below his
standards of sanitation.

c_ea_e_cln_02_01.name: Pest Control Freak
c_ea_e_cln_02_01.explanation:
Determined to rid the city of all pests.
Always ready to flood his immediate
surroundings with toxic pesticides.

c_ea_e_cln_03_01.name: Broke Breakman
c_ea_e_cln_03_01.explanation:
A civil engineer for a shady company
that has yet to pay him. Now resorts to
shakedowns just to make ends meet.

c_ea_e_cln_04_01.name: The Dark Sweeper
c_ea_e_cln_04_01.explanation:
A transcendental custodian. Has judged
humanity to be the source of all pollution.
Seeks to purge them from the earth.

c_ea_e_rep_01_01.name: Twitchy Streamer
c_ea_e_rep_01_01.explanation:
Films whoever he wants for the sake of his
livestream without asking permission.
Will do anything for clicks.

c_ea_e_rep_02_01.name: Popup Paparazzo
c_ea_e_rep_02_01.explanation:
On the hunt for scandalous pictures of
celebrities to sell to the tabloids. Equipped
with a high-end telescopic camera.

c_ea_e_rep_03_01.name: Voyeurchin
c_ea_e_rep_03_01.explanation:
A scumbag who stalks and films women.
Relies on a vast network of hidden
cameras and his own cinematographic skill.

c_ea_e_rep_04_01.name: Creeper Peeper
c_ea_e_rep_04_01.explanation:
A former special-ops member. Now, he
employs his espionage skills to find out
everything about the woman he targets.

c_ea_e_skt_01_01.name: Skaterboi
c_ea_e_skt_01_01.explanation:
A public nuisance who recklessly skates in
places where skateboards are prohibited.
Reprimand him, and he'll throw down.

c_ea_e_skt_02_01.name: Trickmaster
c_ea_e_skt_02_01.explanation:
Pulls off all kinds of dangerous tricks in
public streets. Highly athletic with a
daredevil streak.

c_ea_e_skt_03_01.name: The Wheelman
c_ea_e_skt_03_01.explanation:
A skater who's protected his whole body
so he can run wild on the road. Even
traffic accidents leave him unscathed.

c_ea_e_hpp_01_01.name: New Aged Hippie
c_ea_e_hpp_01_01.explanation:
A busker who sings songs of freedom.
His eccentric performances confuse more
people than they inspire, though.

c_ea_e_hpp_02_01.name: Peacemaker
c_ea_e_hpp_02_01.explanation:
A street musician who specializes in songs
of love. His soothing performances give
passersby a certain peace of mind.

c_ea_e_hpp_03_01.name: Bohemiarch
c_ea_e_hpp_03_01.explanation:
A man who sings and plays songs of peace
in the street. His strange performances
seem to stop people in their tracks.

c_ed_e_snw_01_01.name: Shillboard
c_ed_e_snw_01_01.explanation:
A human billboard who stands in the street
with a sign on him. His hard sell is a little
too aggressive, scaring off customers.

c_ed_e_snw_02_01.name: Killboard
c_ed_e_snw_02_01.explanation:
A salesman who's upgraded his defenses
with a reinforced steel billboard. Bullying
customers is the least of his offenses.

c_ed_e_snw_03_01.name: Invulnera-Billboard
c_ed_e_snw_03_01.explanation:
A legendary salesman said to have been
advertising since time immemorial. His
boards can deflect all kinds of hits.

c_ea_e_wri_01_01.name: Japan Bleacher
c_ea_e_wri_01_01.explanation:
An activist for Bleach Japan. Hasn't quite
got the hang of this "nonviolent protesting"
idea.

c_ea_e_hkc_01_01.name: Beefcake
c_ea_e_hkc_01_01.explanation:
A braggart workout enthusiast. Never wears
too much (so as not to hide his muscles).
Mistakes sick delts for self-esteem.

c_ea_e_hkc_02_01.name: Gym Rat
c_ea_e_hkc_02_01.explanation:
Devoted his life to bodybuilding. His efforts
earned him a truly impressive body, but
now he's looking for an equal rival.

c_ea_e_hkc_03_01.name: Brawnwarden
c_ea_e_hkc_03_01.explanation:
A man who has attained an ultimate body
after years of workouts and steroid use.
Boasts of his invincibility on the streets.

c_ea_e_reg_01_01.name: Pompadork
c_ea_e_reg_01_01.explanation:
A pompadour-styled thug who wanders
the streets. Above all else, hates when
anything musses up his hair.

c_ea_e_reg_02_01.name: Rockabillian
c_ea_e_reg_02_01.explanation:
A thug who dons rockabilly fashion.
Has a real thing for foreign delinquent
culture.

c_ea_e_reg_03_01.name: Johnny Gale
c_ea_e_reg_03_01.explanation:
Boss of the rockabillies. They call him the
Gale cause he's fast and free as the
wind, baby.

c_ea_e_reg_04_01.name: The Twister
c_ea_e_reg_04_01.explanation:
Some say he's the founder of the rockabilly
world. From the fashion to the ideals, it
all began with him.

c_ea_e_sli_01_01.name: City Slicker
c_ea_e_sli_01_01.explanation:
A perverted regular of the Red Light
District. Slopping all that lotion around
got him banned from quite a few stores.

c_ea_e_sli_02_01.name: Grease Monk
c_ea_e_sli_02_01.explanation:
A sage and mentor of the red-light district.
Can manipulate lotion at will, and uses
it to defend himself in sticky situations.

c_ea_e_sli_03_01.name: Pornogra-Pharoah
c_ea_e_sli_03_01.explanation:
A master of all things red-light. An
infamously big spender, he actually runs
his own company by day.

c_ea_e_zom_01_01.name: Imp Patient
c_ea_e_zom_01_01.explanation:
A patient wandering the city after slipping
out of the hospital. Extremely aggressive.
Might be wildly hallucinating.

c_ea_e_zom_02_01.name: Pandemicist
c_ea_e_zom_02_01.explanation:
An escaped hospital patient hellbent on
spreading every contagion he carries.
Resents the healthy.

c_ea_e_zom_03_01.name: The Outlier
c_ea_e_zom_03_01.explanation:
An unfortunate participant in clinical testing
for a new drug gone awry. His body will
never be the same.

c_es_e_exp_01_01.name: Turncoat Titillator
c_es_e_exp_01_01.explanation:
Hides away from busy areas, waiting to
flash unsuspecting passersby. The shock
on their faces turns him on.

c_es_e_exp_02_01.name: Flash Mobber
c_es_e_exp_02_01.explanation:
Once a diligent doctor, he's now awoken to
the thrill of exhibitionism. Inflicting mental
and emotional pain gives him ecstasy.

c_es_e_exp_03_01.name: Crotchety Geezer
c_es_e_exp_03_01.explanation:
Been cited for indecency countless times,
but ran from each charge. Exposes himself
in a way that defies all understanding.

c_ea_e_van_01_01.name: Automoburglar
c_ea_e_van_01_01.explanation:
A group of thieves that targets luxury cars
to steal any valuables within. Known for
forcing doors open with giant crowbars.

c_ea_e_van_02_01.name: Safe Crackpot
c_ea_e_van_02_01.explanation:
Part of a group that sneaks into businesses
and robs safes. They've seen all kinds, and
have a plan for cracking any model.

c_ea_e_van_03_01.name: Undertaker
c_ea_e_van_03_01.explanation:
Tasked with cleaning up those killed in the
underworld. Leaves zero evidence of any
body. Some call him the Cemetery Man.

c_ea_e_dem_01_01.name: Crabby Sentinel
c_ea_e_dem_01_01.explanation:
Guards the condemned thrown into
underground prisons. Formerly a famous
brawler in underground fighting arenas.

c_ea_e_dem_02_01.name: Pier Reviewer
c_ea_e_dem_02_01.explanation:
Secures harborside sites for smuggling
operations with the foreign mafia. Trusted
in the underworld as an intermediary.

c_ea_e_dem_03_01.name: Captain Cruncher
c_ea_e_dem_03_01.explanation:
A man of unknown age who attacks and
pillages fishing boats and cargo ships.
Capable of downing a shark with one blow.

c_ea_e_tro_01_01.name: Slugger
c_ea_e_tro_01_01.explanation:
A giant who charges his enemies with a
flaming bat. Because of his massive size
and recklessness, though, he rarely hits.

c_ea_e_tro_02_01.name: Battering Batter
c_ea_e_tro_02_01.explanation:
A giant who charges his enemies with a
nail Bat. Startlingly agile for his build,
he is skilled in surprise attacks.

c_ea_e_tro_03_01.name: Grand Slammer
c_ea_e_tro_03_01.explanation:
A giant man toting a dangerous barbed wire
bat. One hit from his weapon is enough to
put his victims in critical condition.

c_ea_e_inv_01_01.name: Eccentrickster
c_ea_e_inv_01_01.explanation:
An older fellow who's spent his life on his
hobby of invention. Has been testing his
latest creations on passing street punks.

c_ea_e_inv_02_01.name: Tinkersman
c_ea_e_inv_02_01.explanation:
This old fellow's cooked up all kinds of odd
security equipment... but somehow, none
of them have ever made it to market.

c_ea_e_inv_03_01.name: Edison of Anarchy
c_ea_e_inv_03_01.explanation:
An inventor seemingly possessed by his
own invention. Sees everyone around him
as philistines, and tries to destroy them.

c_ea_e_prp_01_01.name: Dancin' Fool
c_ea_e_prp_01_01.explanation:
Parties anywhere, anytime, to the point
of being a public nuisance. Still, gotta admit,
he has a real gift for shuffle dancing.

c_ea_e_prp_02_01.name: Beat Dropper
c_ea_e_prp_02_01.explanation:
Dances anywhere while blasting EDM at
max volume. Never content to dance solo,
he tries to get others to join in.

c_ea_e_prp_03_01.name: Emperor of Funk
c_ea_e_prp_03_01.explanation:
A legendary dancer from the golden age
of disco. His head-mounted disco ball
keeps the funk alive wherever he goes.

c_ea_e_nrd_01_01.name: Restless Otaku
c_ea_e_nrd_01_01.explanation:
An otaku seeking the touch of an idol's
hand. Extremely wary of thugs, he braces
for a fistfight whenever he sees one.

c_ea_e_nrd_02_01.name: Bag Toter
c_ea_e_nrd_02_01.explanation:
An otaku convinced he has magical
powers. Chants bizarre spells when in
trouble with thugs.

c_ea_e_nrd_03_01.name: Otaku-at-Arms
c_ea_e_nrd_03_01.explanation:
An otaku fully-clad in defensive gear to
ward off thugs. Equipped with +4 Mythril
Badge Armor and a Glowstick of Smiting.

c_ea_e_cut_01_01.name: Bobcutter
c_ea_e_cut_01_01.explanation:
A stubborn beautician whose solution for
any bad haircut is changing it to a bob
cut. Has definite skills as a stylist.

c_ea_e_cut_02_01.name: Fashion Policer
c_ea_e_cut_02_01.explanation:
A bullheaded designer who tries to force
makeovers on those with zero fashion
sense. Keeps fabric shears on hand 24/7.

c_ea_e_cut_03_01.name: Bonsaientist
c_ea_e_cut_03_01.explanation:
An obsessive gardener compelled to prune
all vegetation he sees. His hedge shears
can even slice through tree trunks.

c_ea_e_spr_01_01.name: Weaponologist
c_ea_e_spr_01_01.explanation:
Aims to collect every kind of weapon the
world has to offer. Also looking for an
excuse to test the ones on hand.

c_ea_e_spr_02_01.name: Death Merchant
c_ea_e_spr_02_01.explanation:
An arms dealer in the underworld. He
figures the best way to test out new
inventory is on random passersby.

c_ea_e_spr_03_01.name: Forsaken Samurai
c_ea_e_spr_03_01.explanation:
An armor-clad master of the art of war.
Much to his sorrow, he has no place in
a world of peace and common ground.

c_ea_e_buz_01_01.name: Poacher Egghead
c_ea_e_buz_01_01.explanation:
Poaches any marine life within easy reach.
Often found submerged just nearby the
shoreline.

c_ea_e_buz_02_01.name: Spearheader
c_ea_e_buz_02_01.explanation:
A poacher who can stay underwater for
quite a long time. Uses harpoons to
capture fish with a single shot.

c_ea_e_buz_03_01.name: The Shadow Diver
c_ea_e_buz_03_01.explanation:
A mysterious beach diver who works under
cover of night. Also infiltrates transport
vessels and carries out covert operations.

c_ea_e_ltb_01_01.name: Pseudotrash
c_ea_e_ltb_01_01.explanation:
Lives off dumpster diving. Disguises himself
as a trash bag, partly to have first pick of
any given load of garbage.

c_ea_e_ltb_02_01.name: Toxic Wastoid
c_ea_e_ltb_02_01.explanation:
Suffused with a devastating, overpowering
stench, cultivated over years of generally
being a living affront to hygiene.

c_ea_e_ltb_03_01.name: Gifted Gatherer
c_ea_e_ltb_03_01.explanation:
Built a lucrative and fulfilling life out of
collecting valuable trash. He's rather shy,
though, so he seldom appears in public.

c_ea_e_swg_01_01.name: Ramblin' Man
c_ea_e_swg_01_01.explanation:
A folk musician who roams the city singing.
Being ignored everywhere he goes, however,
brings out his bitter and violent side.

c_ea_e_swg_02_01.name: Guitarsbane
c_ea_e_swg_02_01.explanation:
Destroys his guitar all the time. For him,
that's really the highlight of the show—
he's not even that big on his own music.

c_ea_e_swg_03_01.name: Metal Headsman
c_ea_e_swg_03_01.explanation:
Obsessed with black metal, he calls himself
the devil incarnate. His destructive, anarchic
ideals make him a dangerous musician.

c_ea_e_str_01_01.name: Shaman
c_ea_e_str_01_01.explanation:
Using supernatural abilities, he casts hexes
on the people around him. He is said to
appear at the stroke of midnight.

c_ea_e_str_02_01.name: Bedeviler
c_ea_e_str_02_01.explanation:
A dark shaman nursing a sinister grudge.
Those afflicted by his hexes are certain
to meet with dire misfortune.

c_ea_e_str_03_01.name: High Necromancer
c_ea_e_str_03_01.explanation:
A master of the occult, he has a plethora
of curses at his disposal. Said to be able
to communicate with the dead.

c_e51_excavator.name: Excavator
c_e51_excavator.explanation:
A hydraulic-powered piece of heavy
machinery. These days, crime syndicates
appreciate its value as a "problem solver."

main_sawashiro.name: Jo Sawashiro
main_sawashiro.explanation:
Lieutenant of the Omi Alliance. Said to
be skilled in various martial arts, as befits
an agent of Arakawa the Assassin.

main_tei.name: Zheng
main_tei.explanation:
Member of the Yokohama Liumang. Though
he's hardly a big name, he puffs up in
front of those he deems beneath him.

main_totsuka.name: Yamato Totsuka
main_totsuka.explanation:
Chief of the Yokohama Seiryu Clan. While
a skilled fighter, his true strength is his
willingness to do whatever it takes to win.

main_kantoku.name: Foreman
main_kantoku.explanation:
Overseer of the Yokohama Liumang's
warehouse business. Feared and respected
by even the roughest onsite workmen.

main_takabe.name: Mamoru Takabe
main_takabe.explanation:
Captain of the Yokohama Seiryu Clan.
A reliable ally to his fellow clan
members—in a fight, or otherwise.

main_han.name: Joon-gi Han
main_han.explanation:
An operative affiliated with the Geomijul.
A seasoned martial artist, but also well-
versed in gunplay and knife fighting.

main_mabuchi.name: Akira Mabuchi
main_mabuchi.explanation:
Officer of the Yokohama Liumang. Ruthless
and brutal, he wields Guan Yu's legendary
Green Dragon Crescent Blade with ease.

main_clane.name: Wrecking Ball Crane
main_clane.explanation:
Hydraulic equipment used for demolition.
One hit from its 1-ton wrecking ball, and
any building falls like a house of cards.

main_ishioda.name: Reiji Ishioda
main_ishioda.explanation:
Lieutenant of the Omi Alliance. Revels
in combat, but may swiftly turn volatile
and violent, flying into a savage frenzy.

main_nanba.name: Nanba
main_nanba.explanation:
Relies on skills he picked up from both his
stints as a nurse and as a vagrant. The
kind of guy who'd be a wizard in an RPG.

main_mafia.name: Qing Jin Manager
main_mafia.explanation: Manages Qing Jin. He's torn apart countless lives (and people). Has years of battle and bloodshed behind him.

main_matoba.name: Matoba
main_matoba.explanation:
Officer of the Arakawa Family. A paranoiac
with a morbid obsession for sharp blades.
Can't conceive of getting cut himself.

main_majima.name: Goro Majima
main_majima.explanation:
A man of mystery who loves a good fight.
He toys with foes in a deadly dance, then
tears them apart with his infamous knife.

main_saejima.name: Taiga Saejima
main_saejima.explanation:
A man of mystery with immeasurable
strength. His punches, kicks, and grapples
all hit with devastating impact.

main_mirror.name: Mirror Face
main_mirror.explanation:
A perfect hitman and master of disguise.
However, disguising himself as Adachi led
to a pretty surreal confrontation.

main_tendo.name: Yosuke Tendo
main_tendo.explanation:
Lieutenant of the Omi Alliance. Don't take
his punches lightly—this guy was almost
a world champion of heavyweight boxing.

main_aoki.name: Ryo Aoki
main_aoki.explanation:
Also known as Masato Arakawa. His time
in the United States left him with a host
of vicious combat techniques.

sub_a32_tiger.name: Charlotte
sub_a32_tiger.explanation: A tiger that performs in an animal circus. She's shy, but she seems to listen to Kasuga.

sub_a33_kuma.name: Catherine
sub_a33_kuma.explanation: A bear that performs in an animal circus. Ringmaster Yasuda has been taking care of her for a long time, but she hasn't really taken to him.

sub_a40_sozy.name: Sojimaru
sub_a40_sozy.explanation:
A vacuuming robot invented by Professor
Okita. Moves independently, but strong
enough to vacuum up entire people.

sub_a40_sozy2.name: Seiso Shogun
sub_a40_sozy2.explanation:
A Sojimaru with even higher suction power
after being modded by an unknown saboteur.
It's also far more erratic now.

sub_a05_bier.name: Piss Wizard
sub_a05_bier.explanation:
Used to piss into the river every day.
Public urination was his life's work.

sub_a06_kantoku.name: Machiavellian Manager
sub_a06_kantoku.explanation:
Manager of the Yokohama Shark Stars.
Instigated Anzai into injuring Hanayama,
a player on the opposing team.

sub_a08_gondawara.name: Susumu-chan
sub_a08_gondawara.explanation:
Patriarch of the Gondawara Family, Susumu
Gondawara. A regular at an infant play
brothel, along with (reluctant) subordinates.

sub_a09_mazo.name: Mr. Masochist
sub_a09_mazo.explanation:
Infamously hypermasochistic. A past attempt
at pleasure turned disastrous, hardening
his skin. He has felt no pain since then.

sub_a11_i.name: Il Yu-Jin
sub_a11_i.explanation:
A former Korean megastar. After losing
the limelight due to a scandal, he's been
wallowing in self-pity ever since.

sub_a11_tsuzuki.name: Tsuzuki
sub_a11_tsuzuki.explanation:
Paparazzi who follows Il Yu-Jin trying to
get a scoop. Was trying to extort money
for some scandalous photos he had taken.

sub_a12_jiei.name: Jiei-san
sub_a12_jiei.explanation:
A masked man who spent his nights slicing
up beef. Turned out to be the butcher's son,
who was practicing his butchering skills.

sub_a16_red.name: Red Sujimon
sub_a16_red.explanation:
A Sujimon badgered by Sujimon Sensei
into wearing a red suit.

sub_a16_blue.name: Blue Sujimon
sub_a16_blue.explanation:
A Sujimon bullied by Sujimon Sensei
into wearing a blue suit.

sub_a16_green.name: Green Sujimon
sub_a16_green.explanation:
A Sujimon browbeaten by Sujimon Sensei
into wearing a green suit.

sub_a19_nise.name: Fauxno Michio
sub_a19_nise.explanation:
A poor quality version of the regional
mascot, Ono Michio. Was illicitly selling
counterfeit figures as the genuine article.

sub_a24_gomi.name: Gomi
sub_a24_gomi.explanation:
Owner of a pawn shop. Unable to sell the
items that reminded him of his late wife,
his shop became more of a junk hoard.

sub_a34_yumbo.name: Clara and her Excavator
sub_a34_yumbo.explanation:
A power shovel operated by Clara-chan,
a chimpanzee who normally performs
in an animal circus.

sub_a39_sumo.name: Tosanoyama
sub_a39_sumo.explanation:
A sumo wrestler from a small sumo stable.
Was practicing his tackles on a significant
persimmon tree.

sub_a39_mili.name: Guttersniper
sub_a39_mili.explanation:
A military fanatic. Was practicing his shots
with a brand new toy rifle he purchased
online.

sub_a39_student.name: Locker Warlock
sub_a39_student.explanation:
Tried casting a hex using a straw doll.
Damaged a persimmon tree to curse his "girlfriend" and her lover.

sub_a67_hiroo.name: Hiro
sub_a67_hiroo.explanation:
CEO of PartTimeHero.com. He attacked
Kasuga, mistaking him as the target for
a request to subdue someone.

sub_a71_salary.name: Middling Manager
sub_a71_salary.explanation:
Businessman of a large company. Knows
Ikari from vocational school, but envy
of his intellect consumed him with spite.

sub_a71_stock.name: Traitorous Trader
sub_a71_stock.explanation:
Businessman of a securities company. Knows
Ikari from vocational school, but envy
of his intellect consumed him with spite.

sub_a99_hakase.name: Sujimon Sensei
sub_a99_hakase.explanation:
Dedicates his life to researching Sujimon.
His ultimate goal is to completely fill
the Sujidex.

main_tiger.name: Man-Eating Beast King
main_tiger.explanation: A fierce tiger that was being kept at Qing Jin. It's pristine coat of fur leads one to believe it's well taken care of.
